he way Uyghurs, their supporters and the Chinese state each use technology to their own ends: to set limits and to cross over those limits, respectively. The book provides a granular view of disruptive communication: its sociopolitical moorings and socio-technical control. Findings in this book inform studies of migration and displacement, language and social interaction, advocacy and digital surveillance, and a transnational China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCommunication and technologyzChina. 0aCommunicationxPolitical aspectszChina. 0aUighur (Turkic people)xCommunication. 0aUighur (Turkic people)xPolitics and government. 0aUighur (Turkic people)zChinaxGovernment relations. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aChina.  aUnited States.  aUyghur.  aadvocacy.  adisplacement.  amigration.  asurveillance.  atechnology.  atestimonio.  aunruly communication.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107913270 cprintz978150363339140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363431240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503634312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503634312/original  a978-3-11-079132-7  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 En